ity functions.', 5845, 0), (116113, 'Much popular self-help literature normalizes sexism. Rather than linking habits of being, usually considered innate, to learned behavior that helps maintain and support male domination, they act as those these difference are not value laden or political but are rather inherent and mystical. In these books male inability and/or refusal to honestly express feelings is often talked about as a positive masculine virtue women should learn to accept rather than a learned habit of behavior that creates emotional isolation and alienation.... Self-help books that are anti-gender equality often present women''s overinvestment in nurturance as a ''natural,'' inherent quality rather than a learned approach to caregiving. Much fancy footwork takes place to make it seem that New Age mystical evocations of yin and yang, masculine and feminine androgyny, and so on, are not just the same old sexist stereotypes wrapped in more alluring and seductive packaging.', 218, 0), (116114, 'Conquer all your fears with faith.', 2878, 0), (116115, 'Be true to yourself.', 2878, 0), (116116, 'Body is slave of mind. Mind is regulated by ideas, attitudes, beliefs and tendencies. What really matters is that which set of beliefs get most well entrenched in the mind of a person in the first few decades of his life so as to guide him for the rest of his life as he starts his journey from one end of life to another end of life.', 22619, 0), (116117, 'The past is perception. The future is unknown. The only truth is the present.', 22620, 0), (116118, 'Life is gift. Accepts the sacred existence.', 2878, 0), (116119, 'Keep your hopes high.', 2878, 0), (116120, 'Follow your heart. It will lead you to where you need to be.', 6409, 0), (116121, 'If you don''t know what to do next take the oath that will enhance your soul and erase your ego, & from the quiet space inside yourself, you will know what to do.', 3305, 0), (116122, 'It''s hard to get enough of something that almos