INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (116451, 'What you have suffered after you have healed will make perfect sense.', 5845, 0), (116452, 'You are not, though, forgiving so as to let others off with things. You are forgiving so that you can empower yourself to get over it and become strong.', 5845, 0), (116453, 'The practice of forgiving is a sequential practice that begins with excusing someone.', 5845, 0), (116454, 'As human beings, we are custom made to be happy. Why then would we want to change the order of things by not being happy?', 5845, 0), (116455, 'The pain you feel is simply because you do not yet have the strength to forgive. But you will grow strong again, that is for sure.', 5845, 0), (116456, 'Due to the need to co-exist with these inhuman and inconsiderate people, we will obviously be disturbed by their acts; something which if we look at closely actually means that we too could be affecting some other people negatively every once in a while.', 5845, 0), (116457, 'One way you can trace your way back to real and true happiness and joy is through forgiveness.', 5845, 0), (116458, 'By understanding the basic impediments to forgiveness, the repercussions of failing to forgive and the fruits of forgiveness, this will lead you gently to the shoreline of a distinct new and more powerful YOU.', 5845, 0), (116459, 'Sometimes, we expect life to work a certain way and when it doesn’t we blame others or see it as a sign, rather than face the pain of the choices we should or shouldn’t have made. Real healing won’t begin until we stop saying, “God prevented this or that.” Often in our attempt to protect ourselves from pain, we leave things to fate and don’t take chances. Or, we don’t work hard enough to keep the blessings we are given. Maybe, we didn''t recognize a blessing, until it was too late. Often, it is the lies we tell ourselves that keeps us stuck in a delusion of not being responsible for our lives. We leave it all up to God. The tr